config.json<pre><code>{
  "check_interval_seconds": 600,

  "python_scripts": [
    { "name": "Solution", "process_name": "my_script.py", "enabled": true }
  ],

  "dotnet_apps": [
    { "name": "Dashboard", "process_name": "MyApp.dll", "enabled": false }
  ],

  "linux_services": [
    { "name": "Dashboard",      "service_name": "dashboard.service",      "enabled": true },
    { "name": "ANPR_API",       "service_name": "api.service",            "enabled": true },
    { "name": "Camera_Monitor", "service_name": "camera-monitor.service", "enabled": true }
  ],

  "iis_sites": [
    { "name": "Customer API", "site_name": "CustomerApiPool", "enabled": false }
  ],

  "email": {
    "enabled": true,
    "from_email": "dev@example.com",
    "to_emails": ["admin@example.com"],
    "subject_down": "Service DOWN Alert",
    "subject_recovered": "Service RECOVERED Alert",
    "body_down": "{service_name} has stopped running.",
    "body_recovered": "{service_name} is running again."
  },

  "google_chat_enabled": true,
  "state_file": "service_state.json"
}
</code></pre> Key Type Description <code>check_interval_seconds</code> int Poll frequency in seconds <code>python_scripts</code> list Python processes — matched by command line <code>dotnet_apps</code> list .NET processes — matched by <code>.dll</code> name <code>linux_services</code> list systemd services checked via <code>systemctl</code> <code>iis_sites</code> list IIS app pools checked via PowerShell <code>email.body_down</code> string Supports <code>{service_name}</code> placeholder <code>email.body_recovered</code> string Supports <code>{service_name}</code> placeholder <code>google_chat_enabled</code> bool Enable Google Chat alerts <code>state_file</code> string Path to persisted state JSON <p>Set <code>"enabled": false</code> on any entry to skip it without removing it from config.</p>
